  "author_association": "NONE",
  "body": "As a Kubernetes cluster admin, we would like to manage the deployment and lifecycle of the tiller image to ensure that we control the version of dm backend for our users. \n\nWe are the only one with write access to the `kube-system` namespace and therefore our k8s users are getting errors when trying to run helm init.\n\nFor this reason, we would like to get official manifest files for the deployment and service object. \n\nThis will ensure that we can keep using our current kube-system namespace deployment logic and align the delivery process of kube-system service with the other kubernetes components. \n",
